[?2004l[?2004h> - UIDs appearing in email column
[?2004l[?2004h> - GIDs showing instead of group names
[?2004l[?2004h> - Incorrect data alignment
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Root Causes Identified:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. WRONG DELIMITER FOR emails.dat
[?2004l[?2004h>    - File uses TAB delimiter but script used space delimiter
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Caused entire "uid<TAB>email" to be treated as single field
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Fix: Changed cut -d' ' to awk -F$'\t' for proper tab handling
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. SORTING MISMATCH (noted but already handled via awk lookup)
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Users sorted alphabetically, emails sorted numerically
